        <text>
                <body>
                        <pb n="1"/>
                        <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName>, portion Emor.
                                        <date>5613</date><lb/> (ca. <date>April</date>)</p>
                        <p>May the mountains and the hills carry peace and blessings with–<lb/>out
                                end to my dear and loyal friend, the accomplished and<lb/> learned,
                                whose name is known in the gate of a great city etc.</p>
                        <p>Dear Sir and Friend,</p>
                        <p rend="indent(1)">Again I lift up my pen to reveal to you<lb/> that I and
                                the members of my household are, thank God, well<lb/> and whole. I
                                hope that you too are also in good health, and<lb/> that your
                                spirits will not fail. Now, will you please let me<lb/> know the
                                reason why you have been silent. For I have written<lb/> several
                                times and have as yet had no word in return. What is<lb/> the
                                reason, and what the cause why you turn to me your back<lb/> and not
                                your face. I hope that the <del><add>?</add></del> flame of
                                love<lb/> which used to burn upon the altar of friendship, will not
                                be<lb/> extinguished. Therefore, if you want to do me honor,
                                please<lb/> reply to me.</p>
                        <p rend="indent(1)">Now, will you be good enough to print the<lb/> letter
                                signed by the learned gentleman <persName>Abraham
                                        Benjamini</persName> who<lb/> was a witness at the time when
                                the children of “Bnai Israel”<lb/> were picked to stand an
                                examination. The other letter is by<lb/> myself about the occasion
                                when the school was established to<lb/> teach the Children of Israel
                                (Bnai Israel) to go up on the<lb/> highway that leads to the house
                                of God. If you see that my<lb/> words are correct and will charm the
                                reader, please recount<lb/> the matter in order. The mere printing
                                of the letters will<lb/> achieve much good.<lb/> From your
                                well–wisher and one anxious for<lb/> your
                                        affection<del><add>?</add></del>,<lb/>
                                <persName role="author">Simon ha–Cohen Noht</persName><lb/> Cantor
                                and preacher of Cong.<lb/> Bnai Israel</p>
                </body>
